subject: Re: [Read_Alphabet] Re: Alphabetical Order
msgSnippet: I d vote for keeping Wool and Ooze. They are quite separate sounds in my pronunciation, and spelling both with Ooze would confuse me - for those few words,
messageBody:
I'd vote for keeping Wool and Ooze. They are quite
separate sounds in my pronunciation, and spelling both
with Ooze would confuse me - for those few words,
anyway.

--- Paul Tremblay <phthenry@...> wrote:
> Anthony Grahn wrote:
> On the other hand, since Wool and Ooze cause no
> confusion (unlike On
> Awl, and Ah), we could just as well keep both Wool
> and Ooze.
>
> Paul

===========
Never insult anyone by accident.
- Robert A. Heinlein
